000 \u2013 [[Liam Boyce]] to [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]], 20 June 2017<ref>{{cite news |title=Liam Boyce: Burton sign Ross County striker in club-record deal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40346309 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=20 June 2017 |accessdate=20 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Managers==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Dates\n! Name\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1966\u20131968\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Ian McNeill]]\n| Player-manager\n|-\n| 1968\u20131971\n| ???\n|\n|-\n| 1971\u20131976\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Ian McNeill]]\n| \n|-\n| 1977\u20131979\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Bill Cassidy (footballer, born 1940)|Bill Cassidy]]\n|\n|-\n| 1985\u20131987\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[John Buchanan (footballer born 1951)|John Buchanan]]\n|\n|-\n| 1987\u20131996\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} Robert Wilson \n|\n|-\n| 1 July 1996 \u2013 11 November 2002\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Neale Cooper]]\n|\n|-\n| 27 November 2002 \u2013 11 June 2005\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Alex Smith (footballer born 1939)|Alex Smith]] \n|\n|-\n| 21 June 2005 \u2013 24 October 2005\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[John Robertson (footballer born 1964)|John Robertson]] \n|\n|-\n| 24 October 2005 \u2013 3 June 2006\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Gardner Speirs]] ''(caretaker)'' \n|\n|-\n| 1 July 2006 \u2013 17 June 2007\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Scott Leitch]] \n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Dick Campbell (footballer)|Dick Campbell]] \n|\n|-\n| 2 October 2007 \u2013 11 November 2010\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Derek Adams]] \n|\n|-\n| 11 November 2010 \u2013 25 November 2010\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Craig Brewster]] ''(caretaker)''\n|\n|-\n| 25 November 2010 \u2013 12 February 2011\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Willie McStay (footballer born 1961)|Willie McStay]]\n|\n|-\n| 12 February 2011 \u2013 17 February 2011\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[George Adams (football player and coach)|George Adams]] ''(caretaker)'' \n|\n|-\n| 17 February 2011 \u2013 15 May 2011\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jimmy Calderwood]] \n|\n|-\n| 19 May 2011 \u2013 28 August 2014\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Derek Adams]] \n|\n|-\n| 28 August 2014 \u2013 9 September 2014\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Steven Ferguson (footballer, born 1977)|Steven Ferguson]] ''(caretaker)'' \n|\n|-\n| 9 September 2014 \u2013 25 September 2017\n| {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Jim McIntyre (footballer)|Jim McIntyre]]\n|\n|-\n| 28 September 2017 \u2013 1 March 2018\n| {{flagicon|IRL}} [[Owen Coyle]]\n| First Non-Scottish Manager\n|-\n| 2 March 2018 \u2013 present\n|  {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Steven Ferguson (footballer, born 1977)|Steven Ferguson]]<br/> {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Stuart Kettlewell]]\n| First Co-Managers\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n[[Category:Highland Football League teams]]\n", "text_old": "[[Ross County F.C.|Ross County Football Club]] are a Scottish professional [[association football]] club based in [[Dingwall]]. Ross County joined the [[Highland Football League]] in 1929, and then were one of two clubs voted into the [[Scottish Professional Football League]] System in 1994.\n\nThe club's record appearance maker is [[Michael Gardyne]], who has made Over 400 appearances through four spells at the club. Gardyne is also the club's record goalscorer, scoring over 70 goals in major competitions during his time at Ross County.\n\nThis list encompasses the major honours won by Ross County, records set by the club, their managers and their players.  The player records section includes details of the club's leading goalscorers and those who have made most appearances in first-team competitions. It also records notable achievements by Ross County players on the international stage, and the highest transfer fees paid and received by the club. Attendance records are also included in the list.\n\n==Honours==\n===League===\n* '''[[Scottish Football League First Division|First Division]]/[[Scottish Championship|Championship]] (second tier)'''\n** '''Winners''' (2): [[2011\u201312 Scottish First Division|2011\u201312]], [[2018\u201319 Scottish Championship|2018\u201319]]\n* '''[[Scottish Football League Second Division|Second Division]] (third tier)'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[2007\u201308 Scottish Second Division|2007\u201308]]\n* '''[[Scottish Football League Third Division|Third Division]] (fourth tier)'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[1998\u201399 in Scottish football|1998\u201399]]\n* '''[[Highland Football League]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (3): 1966\u201367, [[1990\u201391 Highland Football League|1990\u201391]], [[1991\u201392 Highland Football League|1991\u201392]]\n** ''Runners-up (2)'': 1967\u201368, 1972\u201373\n* '''[[North Caledonian Football League]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (2): 1965\u201366, 1996\u201397\n\n===Cup===\n* '''[[Scottish Cup]]'''\n** ''Runners-up (1)'': [[2010 Scottish Cup Final|2009\u201310]]\n* '''[[Scottish League Cup]]:'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[2015\u201316 Scottish League Cup|2015\u201316]]\n* '''[[Scottish Challenge Cup|Challenge Cup]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (3): [[2006\u201307 Scottish Challenge Cup|2006\u201307]], [[2010\u201311 Scottish Challenge Cup |2010\u201311]], [[2018\u201319 Scottish Challenge Cup|2018\u201319]]\n** ''Runners-up (2)'': [[2004 Scottish Challenge Cup Final|2004\u201305]], [[2008 Scottish Challenge Cup Final|2008\u201309]]\n* '''[[Scottish Qualifying Cup|Qualifying Cup (North)]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[1993\u201394 Scottish Cup|1993\u201394]]\n** ''Runners-up (5)'': [[1933\u201334 Scottish Cup|1933\u201334]], [[1965\u201366 Scottish Cup|1965\u201366]], [[1969\u201370 Scottish Cup|1969\u201370]], [[1972\u201373 Scottish Cup|1972\u201373]], [[1973\u201374 Scottish Cup|1973\u201374]]\n* '''[[North of Scotland Cup]]'''\n** '''Winners''' (6): 1929\u201330, 1969\u201370, 1971\u201372, 1991\u201392, 2006\u201307, 2018\u201319\n* '''[[Highland League Cup]]'''\n**'''Winners''' (4): 1949\u201350, 1968\u201369, 1978\u201379, 1991\u201392\n\n===Youth===\n* '''[[SPFL Development League]] (Under-20)'''\n** '''Winners''' (1): [[2016\u201317 SPFL Development League|2016\u201317]]\n\n==Player records==\n===Individual Records===\n* '''M