icon|SCO}} [[Richard Brittain]]\n*MF: {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Jackson Irvine]]\n*MF: {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Iain Vigurs]]\n*MF: {{flagicon|SCO}} [[Michael Gardyne]]\n*FW: {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Liam Boyce]]\n*FW: {{flagicon|NED}} [[Alex Schalk]]\n\nSource:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/RossCounty/status/1214155444110987264|publisher=Ross County Twitter|title=Ross County Team of the Decade|date=6 January 2020|accessdate=6 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== International players ===\nThis is a list of former and current players who have played at full international level while with the club and the year of their first International cap while at the club. \n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-3}}\n{{col-end}}\n* 2006 {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Sean Webb]]\n* 2010 {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Michael McGovern]]\n* 2010 {{flagicon|FRO}} [[Atli Gregersen]]\n* 2013 {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Andr\u00e9 Hainault]]\n* 2014 {{flagicon|MTQ}} [[Yoann Arquin]]\n* 2014 {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Filip Kiss]]\n* 2014 {{flagicon|SVK}} [[Erik \u010ciko\u0161]]\n* 2015 {{flagicon|NIR}} [[Liam Boyce]]\n* 2015 {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Jackson Irvine]]\n* 2017 {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Tim Chow]]\n* 2018 {{flagicon|EST}} [[Mattias K\u00e4it]]\n<br>\n*'''Most Caps while at Ross County''': [[Liam Boyce]], [[Atli Gregersen]], [[Yoann Arquin]] (6)\n\n==Club records==\n<ref>{{Cite web|title=Ross County All-Time Records|url=http://www.staggiearchive.co.uk/alltime.php|publisher=Staggies Archive|date=7 October 2019|accessdate=7 October 2019}}</ref>\n* '''First league goal scored''': William D Herd 1994 v [[Cowdenbeath F.C.|Cowdenbeath]]\n* '''Record all-time attendance''': 8,000 approx v [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] ([[Scottish Cup]] 28 February 1966)\n* '''Record league attendance''': 6,590 v [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] ([[Scottish Premiership]] 18 November 2017)\n* '''Record win''': 11\u20130 v [[St Cuthbert Wanderers F.C.|St Cuthbert Wanderers]] ([[1993\u201394 Scottish Cup|1993\u201394 Scottish Cup first round]])\n*'''Record League win''' 8-0 v [[Albion Rovers F.C