{"title_page": "Christie George", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Nigerian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Christie George\n|image          =\n|caption        =\n|fullname       =\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1984|5|10|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = Nigeria\n|height         =\n|position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|youthyears1    =\n|youthclubs1    =\n|years1         = 2008\n|clubs1         = [[Pelican Stars]]\n|caps1          =\n|goals1         =\n|years2         =\n|clubs2         =\n|caps2          =\n|goals2         =\n|totalcaps      =\n|totalgoals     =\n|nationalyears1 = 2008\n|nationalteam1  =[[Nigeria women's national football team|Nigeria]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 0 {{tooltip|(?)|Before 2008 Summer Olympics}}\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n\n'''Christie George''' (born 10 May 1984) is a Nigerian former [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\nShe was part of the [[Nigeria women's national football team]]  at the [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|2008 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/womensolympic/beijing2008/teams/team=1882893/squadlist.html|title=Olympic Football Tournaments Beijing 2008 \u2013 Women / Nigeria |accessdate=25 August 2019|publisher=[[FIFA]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Nigeria at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{FIFA player|265785}}\n* {{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ge/christie-george-1.html |title=Christie George}}\n* {{Soccerway}}\n* http://www.soccerpunter.com/players/19456-Christie-George\n* http://www.gettyimages.com/photos/nigeria-christie-george?excludenudity=true&sort=mostpopular&mediatype=photography&phrase=nigeria%20christie%20george\n\n{{Nigeria squad 2007 FIFA Women's World Cup}}\n{{Nigeria women's football squad 2008 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Nigeria squad 2008 African Women's Championship}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:George, Christie}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian women's footballers]]\n[[Category:Nigeria women's international footballers]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Women's association football forwards]]\n[[Category:2007 FIFA Women's World Cup players]]\n\n\n{{Nigeria-women-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use Nigerian English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Christie George\n|image          =\n|caption        =\n|fullname       =\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|1984|5|10|df=yes}}\n|birth_place    = Nigeria\n|height         =\n|position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|youthyears1    =\n|youthclubs1    =\n|years1         = 2008\n|clubs1         = [[Pelican Stars]]\n|caps1          =\n|goals1         =\n|years2         =\n|clubs2         =\n|caps2          =\n|goals2         =\n|totalcaps      =\n|totalgoals     =\n|nationalyears1 = 2008\n|nationalteam1  =[[Nigeria women's national football team|Nigeria]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 0 {{tooltip|(?)|Before 2008 Summer Olympics}}\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n\n'''Christie George''' (born 10 May 1984) is a Nigerian former [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\nShe was part of the [[Nigeria women's national football team]]  at the [[Football at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's tournament|2008 Summer Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/tournaments/archive/womensolympic/beijing2008/teams/team=1882893/squadlist.html|title=Olympic Football Tournaments Beijing 2008 \u2013 Women / Nigeria |accessdate=25 August 2019|publisher=[[FIFA]]}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Nigeria at the 2008 Summer Olym