={{PAGENAME}}}}\n{{List of cities in Europe}}\n{{Europe topic|List of towns in|MK={{PAGENAME}}}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in North Macedonia|*]]\n[[Category:Lists of cities by country|North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:North Macedonia geography-related lists|Cities]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:Map of the cities of Macedonia-en.svg|thumb|right|300px|Map of the cities in North Macedonia.]]\nThis is a '''list of [[city|cities]] and towns in [[North Macedonia]]'''. In the country there are 34 cities, of which 5 have population of over 50,000 and 12 towns with population of under 10,000 people. The capital city, [[Skopje]], is home to around 25% of the total population of the country. As of 2002, 59.5% of the population lived in urban areas.\nTwelve towns in North Macedonia have population under 10,000: [[Demir Hisar (town)|Demir Hisar]] (2,593), [[Peh\u010devo]] (3,237), [[Demir Kapija]] (3,275), [[Makedonski Brod]] (3,740), [[Valandovo]] (4,402), [[Makedonska Kamenica]] (5,147), [[Kru\u0161evo]] (5,330), [[Bogdanci]] (6,011), [[Kratovo, Macedonia|Kratovo]] (6,924), [[Berovo]] (7,002), [[Probi\u0161tip]] (8,714) and [[Resen (town)|Resen]] (8,748). These towns are officially called \"cities\", but they are often called as \"small towns\" (''\u0433\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0447\u0438\u045a\u0430, grat\u010dinja''), because of the size of the population.\n\nIn North Macedonia there are only 5 cities with population of over 50,000: [[Skopje]] (506,926), [[Bitola]] (74,550), [[Kumanovo]] (70,842), [[Prilep]] (66,246) and [[Tetovo]] (86,580). These are the largest cities in the country.\n\nSeventeen towns in North Macedonia have population between 10,000 and 50,000: [[Veles (city)|Veles]] (43,716),  [[\u0160tip]] (43,652), [[Ohrid]] (42,033), [[Gostivar]] (35,847), [[Strumica]] (35,311), [[Kavadarci]] (29,188), [[Ko\u010dani]] (28,330), [[Ki\u010devo]] (27,067), [[Struga]] (16,559), [[Radovi\u0161]] (16,223), [[Gevgelija]] (15,685), [[Debar]] (14,561), [[Kriva Palanka]] (14,558), [[Sveti Nikole]] (13,746), [[Negotino]] (13,284), [[Del\u010devo]] (11,500) and [[Vinica, Macedonia|Vinica]] (10,863). These towns are often referred to as \"cities of medium size\".\n\n==Statistics==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Largest cities===\nThe largest five cities in North Macedonia are:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!width=\"20px\"|no.!!width=\"60px\"|city!!width=\"70px\"| municipality!!width=\"70px\" |population\n|-\n|1\n| '''[[Skopje]]'''\n| '''[[Greater Skopje]]'''\n|  506,926\n|-\n|2\n| [[Bitola]]\n| [[Bitola Municipality|Bitola]]\n| 74,550\n|-\n|3\n| [[Kumanovo]]\n| [[Kumanovo Municipality|Kumanovo]]\n| 70,842\n|-\n|4\n| [[Prilep]]\n| [[Prilep Municipality|Prilep]]\n| 66,246\n|-\n|5\n| [[Tetovo]]\n| [[Tetovo Municipality|Tetovo]]\n| 52,915\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Smallest towns===\n\nThe five smallest towns in North Macedonia are:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!width=\"20px\"|no.!!width=\"80px\"|city!!width=\"80px\"| municipality!!width=\"70px\" |population\n|-\n|1\n| [[Demir Hisar (town)|Demir Hisar]]\n| [[Municipality of Demir Hisar|Demir Hisar]]\n| 2,593\n|-\n|2\n| [[Peh\u010devo]]\n| [[Peh\u010devo Municipality|Peh\u010devo]]\n| 3,237\n|-\n|3\n| [[Demir Kapija]]\n| [[Demir Kapija Municipality|Demir Kapija]]\n|  3,275\n|-\n|4\n| [[Makedonski Brod]]\n| [[Makedonski Brod Municipality|Makedonski Brod]]\n| 3,740\n|-\n|5\n| [[Valandovo]]\n| [[Valandovo Municipality|Valandovo]]\n| 4,402\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Demographics===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n!width=\"100px\"|city!!width=\"100px\"| municipality!!width=\"60px\" |population!!width=\"100px\" |dominant ethnic group(s)!!width=\"100px\" |% of the dominant ethnic group(s)!!width=\"100px\" |dominant language(s)!!width=\"100px\" |% of the dominant language(s)!!width=\"100px\" |dominant religion!!width=\"100px\" |% of the dominant religion(s)\n|-\n| [[Berovo]] || [[Berovo Municipality|Berovo]] ||7,002 ||[[Macedonians (ethnic g