{"title_page": "Mohamad al-Arefe", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Mohamad al-Arefe\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              = Mohammed Al-Arefe.jpg\n| image_size         = \n| alt                = \n| caption            = \n| native_name        = {{lang|ar|\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a}}\n| native_name_lang   = [[Arabic]]\n| birth_name         = <!-- only use if different from name above -->\n| birth_date         =  {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|7|15}}\n| birth_place        = [[Riyadh]], [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| baptised           = <!-- will not display if birth_date is entered -->\n| disappeared_date   = <!-- {{disappeared date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (disappeared date then birth date) -->\n| disappeared_place  = \n| disappeared_status = \n| death_date         = <!-- {{death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| body_discovered    = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| nationality        = Saudi Arabian\n| other_names        = \n| ethnicity          = <!-- Ethnicity should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = Salafi scholar\n| years_active       = 1990-present\n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          = <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             = <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\" or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight             = <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              = \n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = [[Salafi movement]]\n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| criminal_charge    = <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             = \n| partner            = <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| module             = \n| module2            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_alt      = \n| signature_size     = \n| website            = {{URL|arefe.com}}\n| footnotes          = \n}}\n'''Mohamad bin Abdel-Rahman al-Arefe''' ({{lang-ar|'''\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0631\u062d\u0645\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a'''}}, born [[15 July]] [[1970]]) is a [[Muslim]] [[author]] and [[scholar]]. He is a graduate of [[King Saud University]], and [[member]] of the [[Muslim World League]] and the [[Association of Muslim Scholars]].<ref name=\"IndepHighlights\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/sunni-vs-shia-in-gerrards-cross-new-mosque-highlights-growing-tensions-among-british-muslims-8671969.html|title=Sunni vs Shia... in Gerrard's Cross: New mosque highlights growing tensions among British Muslims|last=Milmo|first=Cahal|date=24 June 2013|work=The Independent|accessdate=25 June 2013}}</ref><ref>[https://www.facebook.com/MArefeEng/info/?tab=page_info Official verified English page, Facebook, 2016].</ref>\n\n== Social media popularity ==\nAl-Arefe has over 20 million followers on [[Twitter]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Yahya |first=Nasidi Adamu |date=19 July 2016 |title=Yadda Malamai ke wa'azi a shafukan zumunta |url=http://www.bbc.com/hausa/news/2016/07/160718_social_media_religious_propagation |newspaper=BBC Hausa |location= |accessdate=}}</ref> As of 6 May 2019, Al-Arefe had over 24 million likes on Facebook,<ref>https://www.facebook.com/3refe/</ref> which places his account in the top 100 worldwide, and #10 in the [[Arab world]] and in the [[Middle East]].<ref>[http://twitaholic.com/ Top Twitter User Rankings] retrieved 3 June 2014</ref> [[BBC]] claims that Al-Arefe is regarded as a clerical \"Brad Pitt\". Al-Arefe announced his fatwa for \"jihad\" against Syrian to his jihadist followers on social media.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=3 March 2016 |title=Meet Saudi Arabia's stars of social media |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/blogs-trending-35609249 |newspaper=BBC Trending |location= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=2 March 2016 |title=Saudis on Social: Faith, Freedom and Fun |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/blogs-trending-35664637 |newspaper=BBC Trending |location= |accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n* He should first admonish her.\n* If admonishing doesn't work he should give her the [[silent treatment]] to show his anger.\n* In the event that those two options fail, a husband may strike his wife (al-Arefe specifically referred to a toothbrush stick [[Miswak]] as an appropriate weapon). \"If he beats her,\" Al-Arefe said, \"the beatings must be light and must not make her face ugly. He should beat her in some places where it will not cause any damage.\"<ref>[http://www.memritv.org/clip_transcript/en/1594.htm MEMRI \u2013 The Middle East Media Research Institute: \"Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-'Arifi Explains Wife Beating in Islam to Young Muslims in a Ramadhan Show\"] Clip No. 1594 \u2013 9 September 2007</ref> 'Ali Al-'Alyani wrote an article responding to Al-Arefe's remarks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/saudi-journalist-saudi-law-banning-wife-beating-supersedes-islamic-law |title= Saudi Journalist: The Saudi Law Banning Wife Beating Supersedes Islamic Law |last= |first= |date= 29 August 2016 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> The Netherlands made Arifi [[persona non grata]] due to this.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/final-appeal-our-2015-summer-campaign-please-support-memri-today |title= Final Appeal For Our 2015 Summer Campaign - Please Support MEMRI Today |last= |first= |date=2 September 2015 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe claimed that Danish women slept around so much that a majority do not know who their father of their children were,{{Citation needed|date=May 2019}} claiming a figure of 54%. No reference was provided. The official figures for unknown fathers incl. sperm donors was 2,1% of all born in 2016.<ref>The Central Person Register and Danmarks Statistik cited by the major newsparer Politiken  6. FEB. 2012 in  \"Far er en ukendt mand for stadig flere b\u00f8rn\". Politiken  http://politiken.dk/forbrugogliv/livsstil/familieliv/art5460723/Far-er-en-ukendt-mand-for-stadig-flere-b%C3%B8rn</ref>  He criticized the west for having magazines, websites, and legal organizations for bestiality and homosexuality and said that sex of all kinds and adultery were practiced by what he called \"infidels\" and compared \"infidels\" to animals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-author-dr-muhammad-al-arifi-show-produced-saudi-ministry-religious-endowments-women-west |title=Saudi Author Dr. Muhammad Al-'Arifi on Show Produced by Saudi Ministry of Religious Endowments: Women in the West Marry Dogs and Donkeys; 54% of Danish Women Do Not Know Who Fathered Their Babies |last= |first= |date=5 April 2006 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/kuwaiti-muslim-brotherhood-leader-and-director-saudi-al-risala-tv-tareq-al-suwaidan-tours |title= Kuwaiti Muslim Brotherhood Leader And Director Of Saudi Al-Risala TV Tareq Al-Suwaidan Tours West, Promoting Restoration Of Caliphate And New Era Of Cyber Jihad |last=Stalinsky |first=Steven |date=14 June 2012 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> Al-Arefe said that there is no bottom limit for the marriageable age of girls.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-islam-does-not-set-minimum-age-marriage |title= Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-'Arifi: Islam Does Not Set a Minimum Age for Marriage |last= |first= |date=4 July 2011 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/memri-tv-archives-child-marriage-arab-muslim-world |title= From The MEMRI TV Archives: Child Marriage In The Arab & Muslim World |last= |first= |date=1 August 2013 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe attacked and criticized the idea of car driving for women.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/saudi-national-dialogue-womens-rights-and-obligations |title= A Saudi National Dialogue on Women's Rights and Obligations |last=Dankowitz |first=Aluma |date=23 June 2004 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe engaged in a diatribe against Shias, referred to them as \"evil\", used the label of \"infidel\" against Shia cleric [[Ayatollah Sistani]] and boasted that there are no mausoleums, public statues, Christian crosses in Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-vilifies-shiites-calling-iraqi-ayatollah-sistani-infidel |title=Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-Arifi Vilifies Shiites, Calling Iraqi Ayatollah Sistani \"an Infidel\" |last= |first= |date=10 December 2009 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> Al-Arefe described Jews as cowardly in battle and claimed that their tanks had urine and feces in them since they wouldn't get out of them.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-jewish-soldiers-would-defecate-and-urinate-their-tanks-because |title=Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-Arifi: Jewish Soldiers Would Defecate and Urinate in Their Tanks Because They Were Too Scared to Leave Them |last= |first= |date=5 February 2012 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> He also claimed they used bags or diapers in the tank.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-israeli-soldiers-too-scared-leave-their-tanks-urinate-or-defecate |title=Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-Arifi: Israeli Soldiers Too Scared to Leave Their Tanks to Urinate or Defecate; Palestine Will Be Liberated Through Force, Not Negotiations |last= |first= |date=9 April 2010 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> He described Jews as too cowardly to fight and said they were going to hide around the Gharqad trees they were allegedly planting.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-jews-plant-gharqad-trees-hide-behind-when-muslims-come-kill-them |title=Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-Arifi: Jews Plant Gharqad Trees to Hide Behind When Muslims Come to Kill Them on Judgment Day |last= |first= |date=11 September 2008 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe said that Muslims should either kill, extract jizya taxes from, or convert \"infidels\" upon invading their lands. He said that Muslims were distracted from \"conquering\" the lands of \"infidels\" by the US's war. He said that a \"believer\" should seek to cut people's legs and arms, break their skulls and cause bloodshed.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-desire-shed-blood-smash-skulls-and-sever-limbs-sake-allah |title= Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-Arifi: 'The Desire to Shed Blood, to Smash Skulls, and to Sever Limbs for the Sake of Allah Is an Honor for the Believer' |last= |first= |date=12 August 2010 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-having-notion-your-heart-shed-blood-smash-skulls-and-chop |title= Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-Arifi: 'Having [the] Notion In Your Heart' to 'Shed Blood, Smash Skulls, and Chop Off Body Parts for the Sake of Allah' is a 'Mark of Honor \u2013 Even If You Do Not Actually Wage Jihad'; Jewish Soldiers Would Defecate and Urinate in T |last= |first= |date=12 March 2012 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> This was a fatwa.<ref>{{cite news |last=Kessler |first=Oren |date=10 May 2012 |title= Saudi clerics use social media to spread hate  |url=http://www.jpost.com/Middle-East/Saudi-clerics-use-social-media-to-spread-hate |newspaper=The Jerusalem Post |location= |access-date= }}</ref>\n\nEither the destruction or reformation of Egyptian President Mubarak was prayed for by Al-Arefe.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/tv/saudi-cleric-muhammad-al-arifi-prays-annihilation-egyptian-president-mubarak |title=Saudi Cleric Muhammad Al-'Arifi Prays for the Annihilation of Egyptian President Mubarak |last= |first= |date=4 July 2010 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe repudiated allegations that he said that \"mujahideen\" in the Syrian Civil War could have provided with sex by emigrant Muslim women.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/tunisian-daily-al-shurouqs-campaign-against-sexual-jihad |title= Tunisian Daily Al-Shurouq's Campaign Against 'Sexual Jihad' |last=Chernitsky |first=B. |last2=Goldberg |first2=R. |date=1 February 2014 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe supported the [[Muslim Brotherhood]] in Egypt.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/saudi-authorities-irate-over-communiqu%c3%a9-condemning-ouster-former-egyptian-president-mursi |title= Saudi Authorities Irate Over Communiqu\u00e9 Condemning Ouster Of Former Egyptian President Mursi |last=Admon |first=Y. |date=8 October 2013 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> Al-Arefe was lauded by Egyptian Muslim Brotherhood President Mursi and al-Arefe and [[Salman al-Ouda]] were named as Muslim Brotherhood sympathizers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/saudi-prince-about-kingdoms-muslim-brotherhood-movement-they-are-khawarij-age |title= Saudi Prince About Kingdom's Muslim Brotherhood Movement: They Are The Khawarij Of This Age |last= |first= |date=28 August 2013 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> He is a known associated of them.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.memri.org/espanol/controversia-en-el-mundo-arabe-sobre-el-visitar-lugares-cristianos-y-musulmanes-en-israel/7720 |title=Controversia en el mundo \u00e1rabe sobre el visitar lugares cristianos y musulmanes en Israel |last= |first= |date=23 May 2014 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate=25 January 2017 |quote=}}</ref>\n\nMuslim Brotherhood affiliation was denied for Arefe and [[Adil al-Kalbani]] by al-Kalbani, saying that they are affiliated with the Union of Muslim Scholars.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=19 August 2013 |title=\u062a\u062a\u0635\u0641\u062d \u0627\u0644\u0622\u0646: \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0644\u0628\u0627\u0646\u064a : \u0623\u0646\u0627 \u0639\u0636\u0648 \u0641\u064a \u0627\u062a\u062d\u0627\u062f \u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0633\u0644\u0645\u064a\u0646 \u0648\u0644\u0633\u062a \u0625\u062e\u0648\u0627\u0646\u064a\u0627\u064b .. \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a \u0644\u064a\u0633 \u0625\u062e\u0648\u0627\u0646\u064a\u0627\u064b |url=http://www.an7a.com/115868/ |newspaper=\u0635\u062d\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u0623\u0646\u062d\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0644\u0643\u062a\u0631\u0648\u0646\u064a\u0629 |location= |access-date= }}</ref>\n\nA video Al-Arefe was posted by Ibrahim al-Musalem on a tweet about the [[Charlie Hebdo shooting]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/reactions-twitter-attack-charlie-hebdo-%E2%80%93-including-hashtags-paris-burning-vengeance |title= Reactions On Twitter To Attack On 'Charlie Hebdo' \u2013 Including Hashtags #Paris Is Burning, #Vengeance For [Insulting] Allah's Messenger, #Lone Wolves Are Terrorizing France |last= |first= |date=9 January 2015 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nHoliday celebrations and greetings to Christians by Muslims was banned by Al-Arefe.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www2.memri.org/espanol/periodista-jordana-el-odio-hacia-los-cristianos-es-el-primer-paso-en-el-camino-hacia-el-terrorismo/9842 |title=Periodista jordana: El odio hacia los cristianos es el primer paso en el camino hacia el terrorismo |last= |first= |date=24 December 2015 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> He strictly explicitly banned religious greetings to non-Muslims.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/president-sisi-egyptian-grand-mufti-offering-christmas-greetings-our-christian-brothers-part |title= President Sisi, Egyptian Grand Mufti: Offering Christmas Greetings To Our Christian Brothers Is Part Of Our Religion |last= |first= |date=24 December 2015 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref> Al-Arefe forbade the usage of [[Christmas trees]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/MohamadAlarefe/status/811265656511459328 |title= |last=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a |first=\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f |date=20 December 2016 |website=Twitter |publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nHe said that Syria jihad is incumbent and did apologia for [[al-Nusra]], visiting the [[Imam Muhammad ibn Abd al-Wahhab Mosque]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/qatar/11125897/The-Club-Med-for-terrorists.html|title=The 'Club Med for terrorists' |newspaper=The Telegraph|date=27 September 2014|last=Gilligan|first=Andrew}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2015, Al-Arafe wrote a critique<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/3refe/posts/10153284714117839|title=\ud83d\udeab \u0627\u0644\u0622\u0628\u0627\u0621 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0623\u0628\u0646\u0627\u0621 \u0648\u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u0628\u064a\u0646 \u0648\u0648\u0642\u0641\u0627\u062a \u0645\u0639... \u2013 \u0627\u0644\u0635\u0641\u062d\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0633\u0645\u064a\u0629 \u0644\u0644\u0634\u064a\u062e \u062f. \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a . \u2013 Facebook|author=|date=|work=facebook.com|language=Arabic}}</ref> on Facebook of the Egyptian Ramadan TV series Jewish Quarter, complaining that it showed Jews in a positive light, when in reality Jews were terrible people. It was picked up by Arabic media.\n\nIn March 2014, he was banned by the [[Home Office]] from returning to Britain after a series of sermons in [[Cardiff]], Birmingham and London. A Home Office spokesperson said: \"We can confirm Mohammad Al-Arefe has been excluded from the United Kingdom. The Government makes no apologies for refusing people access to the UK if we believe they represent a threat to our society. Coming here is a privilege that we refuse to extend to those who seek to subvert our shared values.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Banned preacher under scrutiny over links to young Cardiff men fighting with Isis in Iraq and Syria|url=http://www.itv.com/news/2014-06-23/banned-preacher-under-scrutiny-over-links-to-young-cardiff-men-fighting-with-isis-in-iraq-and-syria/|date=23 June 2014|work=ITV|accessdate=26 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Father of Cardiff jihadists says his sons were radicalised in 'pop-up' schools|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2014/jun/23/father-jihadists-sons-radicalised-cardiff-popup-schools|date=23 June 2014|work=Guardian|accessdate=26 December 2014 |first=Steven |last=Morris}}</ref>\n\nAl-Arefe had a discussion with Saudi [[Deputy crown prince]] [[Mohammad bin Salman Al Saud]] and then tweeted and posted a photo of them smiling together.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/mohamadalarefe/status/724662086308126720?lang=en |title=\u062f. \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f #\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a on Twitter |last=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a |first=\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f |date=25 April 2016 |website=Twitter |publisher= |accessdate=25 January 2017 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=25 April 2016 |title=\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631 24 &#124; \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a \u064a\u0646\u0634\u0631 \u0635\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0631\u0641\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u064a\u0631 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0646 |url=http://akhbaar24.argaam.com/article/detail/277576 |newspaper=\u0623\u062e\u0628\u0627\u0631 24 |location= |accessdate=}}</ref> The discussion was held on the same day as [[Saudi Vision 2030]] began.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=27 April 1438 |title= \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a \u064a\u0646\u0634\u0631 \u0635\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0631\u0641\u0642\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0623\u0645\u064a\u0631 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0646 \"\u0631\u0624\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f\u064a\u0629\" |url=http://saabag.com/news-action-show-id-14808.htm |newspaper=\u0635\u062d\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u0633\u0627\u0628\u0642 \u0627\u0644\u0625\u0644\u0643\u062a\u0631\u0648\u0646\u064a\u0629 |location= |accessdate= }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=\u0639\u064a\u0633\u0649 |first=\u0639\u0645\u0631 |date=25 April 2016 |title=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a\" \u064a\u0634\u0643\u0631 \u0648\u0644\u064a \u0648\u0644\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0647\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f\u064a \u0644\u0647\u0630\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0628\u0628 |url=http://www.cairoportal.com/story/542570/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B4%D9%83%D8%B1-%D9%85%D8%AD%D9%85%D8%AF-%D8%A8%D9%86-%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%84%D9%87%D8%B0%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B3%D8%A8%D8%A8 |newspaper=\u0628\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0642\u0627\u0647\u0631\u0629 |location= |accessdate=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=25 April 2016 |title= \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a \u064a\u0644\u062a\u0642\u064a \u0645\u0639 \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0633\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a \u0645\u0646 \u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0646 \u0631\u0624\u064a\u0629 2030 |url=http://alkhaleejonline.net/articles/1461609992083616200/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%AA%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A8%D9%86-%D8%B3%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D9%85%D9%86-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%B1%D8%A4%D9%8A%D8%A9-2030/ |newspaper=\u0627\u0644\u062e\u0644\u064a\u062c \u0623\u0648\u0646\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0646 |location=\u0627\u0644\u0631\u064a\u0627\u0636 |accessdate=}}</ref> He asked God to bless Prince Mohammad and posted his thanks.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= <!--|date= 25 \u0623\u0628\u0631\u064a\u0644, 2016 , 22:11 \u0645 -->|title=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a \u064a\u0646\u0634\u0631 \u0635\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0631\u0641\u0642\u0629 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0639\u062f \u0625\u0639\u0644\u0627\u0646 \"\u0631\u0624\u064a\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f\u064a\u0629\" |url=https://al-marsd.com/33645.html |newspaper=\u0635\u062d\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u0635\u062f |location= |accessdate=}}</ref> al-Arefe met with Prince Mohamed bin Salman again and talked with him and posted the photo of them smiling together on Twitter.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/MohamadAlarefe/status/811510213199204352 |title=\u062f. \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f #\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a on Twitter |last=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a |first=\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f |date=21 December 2016 |website=Twitter |publisher= |accessdate=25 January 2017 |quote=}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=22 December 2016 |title=\u0627\u0644\u0634\u064a\u062e \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a \u064a\u0646\u0634\u0631 \u0635\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u062c\u0645\u0639\u062a\u0647 \u0628\u0640 \u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646.. \u0648\u064a\u0643\u0634\u0641 \u0645\u0627 \u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0628\u064a\u0646\u0647\u0645\u0627 |url=http://mz-mz.net/686775/ |newspaper=\u0645\u0640\u0632\u0645\u0640\u0632 |location= |accessdate= }}</ref> They talked about the Islamic world's and the Kingdom (of Saudi Arabia's) future.<ref>{{cite news |last= |first= |date=22 December 2016 |title=\u0627\u0644\u0634\u064a\u062e \"\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a\" \u064a\u0646\u0634\u0631 \u0635\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u062c\u0645\u0639\u062a\u0647 \u0628\u0640\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0633\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0646 .. \u0648\u064a\u0643\u0634\u0641 \u0645\u0627 \u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0628\u064a\u0646\u0647\u0645\u0627 |url=https://al-marsd.com/91951.html |newspaper=\u0635\u062d\u064a\u0641\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0631\u0635\u062f |location= |accessdate=25 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n[[King Saud University]] employs Al-Arefe.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gulfinstitute.org/saudi-deputy-crown-prince-meets-obama-after-welcoming-an-isis-supporter/ |title=Saudi Deputy Crown Prince Meets Obama after Welcoming an ISIS Supporter |author=IGA Staff |date=17 June 2016 |website=The Institute for Gulf Affairs |publisher= |accessdate= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nArifi on Twitter vowed for Russia and Assad to be defeated over the [[Aleppo offensive (November\u2013December 2016)|Battle of Aleppo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/MohamadAlarefe/status/808732352662925312 |title= |last=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a |first=\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f  |date=13 December 2016 |website=Twitter |publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>\n\nCondolences over the death of the son of [[Salman al-Ouda]] and his wife were given on Twitter by Mohamad al-Arefe.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/MohamadAlarefe/status/824339078422429696 |title= |last=\u0627\u0644\u0639\u0631\u064a\u0641\u064a |first=\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f |date=25 January 2017 |website=Twitter |publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>\n\n[[Abdul Razzaq al-Mahdi]], Nabil Al-Awadi, [[Tariq Abdelhaleem]], and [[Hani al-Sibai]] who are linked to Al-Qaeda, in addition to others like [[Adnan al-Aroor]], [[Abd Al-Aziz Al-Fawzan]], Mohamad al-Arefe, [[Abdul Rahman Al-Sudais]], [[Abdul-Aziz ibn Abdullah Al Shaykh]] and others were included on a death list by ISIS.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.memri.org/reports/isis-launches-campaign-calling-kill-prominent-islamic-clerics-such-yousuf-al-qaradawi-saudi |title= ISIS Launches Campaign Calling To Kill Prominent Islamic Clerics Such As Yousuf Al-Qaradawi, Saudi Mufti 'Abd Al-'Aziz Aal Al-Sheikh, Former Egyptian Chief Mufti 'Ali Gum'a  |last=|first= |date=14 February 2017 |number=Special Dispatch No.6781 |website=MEMRI |publisher= |access-date= |quote=}}</ref>\n\n=== The 2013 Egyptian coup d'\u00e9tat ===\n{{BLP unsourced section|date=April 2015}}\nIn July 2013, Al-Arefe was detained by the Saudi authorities for using YouTube to criticize the military coup d'\u00e9tat in Egypt, an ally of Saudi Arabia.<ref name=CSM>[http://www.csmonitor.com/World/Middle-East/2015/0602/Saudi-Arabia-presses-YouTube-imams-to-toe-the-line-on-Yemen Christian Science Monitor: \"Saudi Arabia presses 'YouTube imams' to toe the line on Yemen \u2013 Popular Muslim clerics are using social media to stir dissent beyond the purview of government-controlled mosques and satellite TV stations. Saudi Arabia is sensitive to criticism of its war in Yemen\" By Taylor Luck] 2 June 2015</ref> It was speculated{{by whom|date=April 2015}} that the arrest was in response to a complaint filed by the Egyptian Ministry of Foreign Affairs to its Saudi counterpart. The complaint claimed that Al-Arefe was intervening in Egyptian domestic affairs.{{verify-inline|date=April 2015}} Before his release, he signed a pledge not to interfere in Egyptian affairs and was released afterwards but placed under house arrest. He was also banned from traveling to [[Doha]], where he was scheduled to deliver a religious lecture there. The Saudi authorities never announced the reason behind Al-Arefe's arrest.\n\n== Sanctions ==\nIn October 2014, he was jailed for 40 days for stating that the train linking [[Mecca]] and other holy sites was \"one of the worst in the world\".<ref name=CSM /> Al-Arefe was banned from entering Switzerland for holding extreme views, Switzerland said.<ref name=IndepHighlights/>\n\nDenmark banned him from entering the country for two years in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nyidanmark.dk/en-GB/Words-and-concepts/US/Religious-workers/Religious-preachers-with-entry-ban/?anchor=7C5D2D143D284E4EB2829BA5F0F04837&callbackItem=8ADE78BB86084E60B9A89B35BDDCDDAE&callbackAnchor=8ADE78BB86084E60B9A89B35BDDCDDAE|title=Den nationale sanktionsliste - Religious preachers with entry ban|website=www.nyidanmark.dk|language=Danish|access-date=2019-02-14}}</ref><ref name=\"Reuters-20170502\">{{cite web |last1=Jensen |first1=Teis |title=Denmark bans six 'hate preachers' from entering the country |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-denmark-security-religion/denmark-bans-six-hate-preachers-from-entering-the-country-idUKKBN17Y1N9 |publisher=[[Reuters]] |accessdate=13 April 2019 |date=2 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|Islam|Saudi Arabia}}\n{{Commons category|Mohamad al-Arefe}}\n\n* [[Islam in Saudi Arabia]]\n* [[Yusuf al-Qaradawi]]\n* [[Salman al-Ouda]]\n* [[Aid al-Qarni]]\n* [[Mohammed Rateb al-Nabulsi]]\n* [[Tareq Al-Suwaidan]]\n* [[Omar Abd al-Kafi]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*https://www.arefe.com \n*https://twitter.com/MohamadAlarefe\n*https://plus.google.com/110212684724359342394\n*